Baseball Statistic

Most famous baseball statistic

\[ \text{Batting Avg} = \frac{\text{Hits}}{\text{At Bats}} \]

which is a form of proportion \(p\):

  • \(\text{Hits}\): success
  • \(\text{At Bats}\): Attempts at a Hit

Define Empirical Prior

We use only those batters with at least 500 At Bats. The prior mean batting avg is 0.259

Define Empirical Prior

Let's assume the prior is Beta\((\alpha, \beta)\). We find the MLE's \((\widehat{\alpha}, \widehat{\beta}) = (78.971, 225.887)\)
